				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document} $$ Ent(D)=-\sum_{k=m,n}^{} p_{k} \log_{2} p_{k}  $$ \end{document}Ent(D)=−∑k=m,npklog2pk

In the boundary identification, all samples are re-classified by the gene expression level with a split point of x and Dv denotes the new dataset re-classed by x. Then the information gain of this split point can be computed as:
